Veteran radio journalist Waweru Mburu will be buried on Friday in his farm at Punda milia, Maragua constituency.A funeral service will be held at Murang'a Teachers College.Mburu was working as the head of Radio Citizen at Royal Media Services at the time of his demise.He passed on at MP Shah Hospital while undergoing treatment on September 28.The voice behind the Yaliyotendeka show on Citizen Radio is said to have been battling gastric cancer.Read: Citizen Radio journalist Waweru Mburu is deadMburu had recently declared his bid to vie for Maragua Constituency MP seat.Also read: Politicians, journalists join Kenyans in mourning radio presenter Waweru Mburu